article.description: Rhode Island beats UMass 75-69, takes half-game A-10 lead
article.headline: Rhode Island beats UMass 75-69, takes half-game A-10 lead
article.linkText: Rhode Island beats UMass 75-69, takes half-game A-10 lead
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. -- E.C. Matthews scored 16 points and Hassan Martin added 11 points and 10 rebounds to help Rhode Island beat Massachusetts 75-59 and take a half-game lead in the Atlantic 10. The Rams (18-6, 10-3) are a half-game ahead of Dayton and VCU, both at 9-3. UMass (16-10, 9-4) fell out of what was a four-way for first place. Jered Terrell added 14 points and Jarvis Garrett 13 for Rhode Island, which beat the Minutemen for the first time in eight meetings. UMass beat the Rams at home 60-56 on Jan. 17. Martin's double-double was his seven this season and 11th of his career. He also had four blocks. Jabarie Hinds scored 17 points, Derrick Gordon 15 and Donte Clark 14 for UMass with Cady Lalanne grabbing 10 rebounds. Rhode Island went on a 9-0 run to lead 45-30 with 13:26 remaining. The Minutemen never got closer than nine after that.
